Irish Beef and Guinness Stew!! Yup there’s Guinness stout in it and it makes the beef stew all the more so delicious🍺⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Ingredients:⁣⁣
4 cloves garlic, minced⁣⁣
2 Medium onions, sliced ⁣⁣
3 tbsp oil⁣⁣
1.4kg beef shin, cut into 2” chunks⁣⁣
Salt and Pepper⁣⁣
3 tbsp flour⁣⁣
500ml Guinness stout ⁣⁣
4 tbsp tomato paste⁣⁣
750ml chicken or beef stock⁣⁣
5 medium carrots, peeled and cut into 1” chunks⁣⁣
4 celery stalks, cut into 1” chunks⁣⁣
1 tsp Worcester sauce ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Steps:⁣⁣
1)Make sure the beef shin slices are dry before seasoning with salt and pepper on both sides⁣⁣
2)Heat a Pot with 3 tbsp oil and sear the beef about 2.5mins on each side until brown. Repeat with all the slices⁣⁣
3)Remove beef and set aside on a separate plate.⁣⁣
4)In the same pot, there should be some remaining oil. Cook the garlic and onions until slightly soften⁣⁣
5)Add in the flour and stir to cook it for abit for 1-2 mins⁣⁣
6)Add the chicken/beef stock, Guinness stout and tomato paste and stir until well mix⁣⁣
7)Add back the beef into the pot and heat until boiling ⁣⁣
8)Transfer pot into a slow cooker and continue cooking for 7-8 hours until the beef is fork tender. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Notes: You can also cook this beef stew using a cast iron pot like Le Creuset. Instead of slow cooking it, lower the heat after you add back the beef to the pot, cover lid and cook for 3-4hours (Stirring every 30mins or so) At the last hour, remove lid and cook until liquid has reduced and the gravy would have thicken up a little. ⁣⁣
